paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted information on the TTR gene variant rs1667255, including its association with serum retinol levels and head and neck cancer risk.

functional_data.summary: The level of serum retinol increased significantly with the number of minor alleles for TTR rs1667255 among controls.
assays: High performance liquid chromatography for serum retinol measurement

variants.segregation_data: Not applicable as no segregation data provided.
variants.additional_notes: No significant association between TTR rs1667255 and HNC risk was observed.
key_quotes: The level of serum retinol increased significantly with the number of minor alleles for TTR rs1667255 among controls.
In contrast, serum retinol levels were not associated with TTR rs1667255 among HNC cases.

extraction_metadata.notes: Only one variant in the TTR gene was reported in the paper.
